23/11/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- The EU defence ministers struck a deal Monday (22 November) on the future formation of 13 battle groups, which would intervene with NATO in dealing with crisis situations around the world. According to press reports in Athens, Greece is to be grouped with Italy, Portugal and Spain in one of these future units, each of which would include up to 1,500 troops. (Kathimerini - 23/11/04; MPA - 22/11/04)
